#
# Configuration for country-based traffic blocking.
# This is an example file. Add the country codes you wish to block.
# Use this configuration at your own risk. Firewall rules can lock you out,
# interrupt legitimate traffic, or break services if they are too broad.
# Review the generated rules before applying them, especially on remote hosts.
#
# Format: <country-codes> <chains> <ip-versions>
#
# <country-codes>: Comma-separated list of two-letter country codes (e.g., ru,ir,cn)
# <chains>: Comma-separated list of chains: input, output, forward, or * for all
# <ip-versions>: Comma-separated list: v4, v6, or * for both
#
# Examples:
# ru,ir * *
# cn input v4
